# Linux Boot Process
    - BIOS
    - BOOTLOADER
    - Linux KERNEL
    - Runlevels

# BIOS
    - Basic I/O sys
    - special firmware
    - it is Operating System Independent
    - primary process is to find & execute the 'Boot Loader'
    - Perform the POST
        - Power On Self Test
        - POST checks CPU, Memory, Storage Device

    - Once POST success -> BIOS run BootLoader

    - bootable deveice: Hard Dirve, USB Drive, DVD Drive etc.

# BOOT LOADER
    - LILO (Old Method)
        -> Linux Loader
    
    - GRUB
        - Grand Unified BOOT Loader
        - replace LILO

    - Bootloader start the OS.
    
# Intital RAM Disk
    - intird    ::   initial RAM Disk
    - contain helper & module req to load OS file sys

# /boot dir
    - contain files req to boot linux
    - initrd
    - kernel
    - boot loader config

    - ls -F /boot
